<content type="str">The Nigerian Islamic preacher who married about 93 wives, Alhaji Mohammed Abubakar Bello Masaba, is died. 
 
Masaba who slumped twice Saturday morning, later died in the afternoon around 2pm after a brief illness in his Bida, Niger State residence at the age of 93. 
 
His Personal Assistant, Alhaji Mutairu Salawudeen Bello, confirmed the death to The Eagle Online. 
 
“With gratitude to Allah (SWT), we announce the death of Alhaji Mohammed Abubakar Bello this afternoon,” he said. 
 
“He was aged 93 years. He died after a brief illness. 
 
“The Janiza prayer and interment is slated for tomorrow (Sunday) by 10am.” 
 
The aide added that Pa Masaba fore-told his death and was prepared for it. 
 
Bello said: “Baba had told us that his time was up. He told me personally during his last moment that he has completed his divine assignment and was ready to meet his creator. 
 
“He told us to remain dedicated to the cause of Islam and urged us all not to deviate from all his teachings on righteousness, piety and total submission to the will of Allah. 
 
“He warned us to shun adultery, but that we should marry our women because it is ‘Hallal’ before Allah.” 
 
